@Ocado I have already spoken to Ocado on numerous occasions and it just keeps happening.

I only took the photos because I was embarrassed to keep claiming.

The apples are from the ethical food company. They used to be packed in a cardboard tray but now just a cellophane bag.

@Halfords_uk I have been without my electric bike for nearly 2 months. I have mobility issues &amp; it is much needed. Please see longer thread Tweet for details.

The battery is faulty and you have not been able to supply an awake one.

This problem began on the 2 nd of November. https://t.co/OixKZkA2RZ

@GrimArtGroup thanks for the encouragement to share &amp; thanks to everyone who supported my last efforts:

Yesterday I fogot to say I was also in love with patched brick walls, overgrown doors, scrapped vehicles &amp; incongruous junk.

Never had anywhere to share these before, thanks. https://t.co/Z7Q9J7dMBd

@Maro2Bear As they say size isn't everything, I'm sure there will be other categories. I was rather hoping to bag artistic merit!

I do fear for the larger varieties in my garden as the wind can whip across. Sadly they could fall at the final fence.

Happy growing. :)

@womensart1 I believe they transitioned from one type of plane to another on a daily basis, this is a difficult thing to do. They delivered 147 different types of planes during WWII.

https://t.co/5mh6RNMPIP

They helped win the Battle of Britain by freeing airmen to fight. #LestWeForget

@LunarLast In times of mental anquish I like this. It is about self compassion and wishing the best for yourself.

'Compassion like gently falling rain touches everything.'

I found it in a book called The Buddah's Brain.
